Installing Quizki on a completely new DigitalOcean droplet.

Assuming Ubuntu 14.04.

1) Add the Quizki user - 
> sudo adduser quizki --gecos "First Last,RoomNumber,WorkPhone,HomePhone" --disabled-password
> echo "quizki:password" | sudo chpasswd
> sudo adduser quizki sudo

2) Login as the Quizki user

3) Get the quizki git repository
> cd ~
> mkdir apps
> cd apps
> sudo apt-get install git
> git clone https://github.com/haxwell/quizki.git

4) Run the Quizki install script
> cd quizki 
> sudo ./install-droplet.sh


